The subject focuses on helping students develop a personal life plan that aligns with their values, goals, and aspirations. The application of self-management tools is learned. At the end of the subject, the learner is consciously ready to shape his/her/their career and working life, is able to set goals both in his/her/their personal life and in his professional life, and has a clear vision of how to achieve these goals.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to provide an overview of possible self-management tools and learn to apply them in your life.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: *develops an understanding of personal values, goals and aspirations; *has acquired skills and tools for self-development; *applies learned methods to personal and professional challenges *is able to adapt to changes and make informed decisions; *can set goals and plan ways to fulfill them.
